^ O'Connor, John J.; Robertson, Edmund F., “Sharaf al-Din al-Muzaffar al-Tusi”, MacTutor History of Mathematics archive, University of St Andrews, http://www-history.mcs.st-andrews.ac.uk/Biographies/Al-Tusi_Sharaf.html .
^ Victor J. Katz (1995), "Ideas of Calculus in Islam and India", Mathematics Magazine 68 (3): 163-174 [165-9 & 173-4]
^ Eves, Howard (1990). An Introduction to the History of Mathematics. Saunders Series (6th ed.). Philadelphia: Saunders College Publishing. 



J. Edwards (1892). Differential Calculus. London: MacMillan and Co.. http://books.google.com/books?id=unltAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA1#v=onepage&q&f=false. 






